Title: Arm is giving Qualcomm the wake-up call it needs
summary:
Summary Agent: 
Arm, the company behind processor architecture in most phones and tech devices, has given Qualcomm a 60-day notice to stop making chips due to alleged breaches of their license agreement. Both companies are in a legal dispute, but it is likely they will come to an agreement before Qualcomm halts production, as Qualcomm heavily relies on Arm. The consequences of Qualcomm discontinuing chip production would have a significant impact on various industries and consumers, making reaching a resolution crucial for both companies and the market.
